Smithing is not a main cultural tradeskill for halflings, but rather a way to make items that they need to perform their tailoring. As such, it's not as important to obtain ludicrously high levels of skill before performing these combines in the Vale forge. However, for the sake of your sanity, and your pocketbook, you'll want to obtain at least a small amount of proficiency in working with molten metals before you try these combines.<p>
As will all cultural tradeskills, the Vale forge requires that combines are performed by halflings, and only halflings.  Illusions do not fool any cultural tradeskill container.<br><div align="right">Last Modified By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>

		Last Modified on: 2003-05-19 06:28:05&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
